cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel attention mechanism for 3D medical image segmentation using a cascade of a detection module followed by a segmentation module. This approach is related to computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves object detection and segmentation. The use of attention mechanisms also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the proposed method to medical data further suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural engineering (cs.NE).
